  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "HR Executive",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Summary</strong></p><p>Lead and execute comprehensive HR functions including onboarding, payroll administration, employee records management, and compliance to drive workforce productivity and support organizational growth.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Administer monthly payroll processing and ensure accurate CPF submissions to achieve full statutory compliance</li><li>Manage leave and attendance tracking to maintain accurate workforce data and support operational efficiency</li><li>Oversee employee benefits administration to enhance employee satisfaction and retention</li><li>Coordinate performance appraisal and training administration to facilitate employee development aligned with organizational goals</li><li>Respond promptly to employee enquiries and resolve HR-related issues to foster a positive and supportive work environment</li><li>Ensure strict adherence to Ministry of Manpower (MOM) regulations and company policies to mitigate compliance risks</li><li>Maintain accurate and up-to-date HR documentation and generate reports to inform management decisions and support audits</li></ul><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Human Resources, Business Administration, or related field</li><li>1–3 years of HR experience demonstrating practical application of HR functions</li><li>Knowledge of Singapore employment laws and HR best practices</li><li>Experience with payroll and CPF submissions</li><li>Proficient in MS Word, Excel, and HR information systems</li><li>Strong communication and interpersonal skills applied to employee engagement and stakeholder collaboration</li><li>Detail-oriented and organized with the ability to work independently and manage multiple priorities</li></ul>",
